# Databricks Chatbot Application

A modern, responsive chat interface that connects to Databricks AI serving endpoints, built with Dash and Python.

## Features

- Easy deployment as a Databricks App
- Real-time chat interactions with Databricks AI models
- Ability to collect user feedback on the responses
    - Thumbs up / Thumbs down
    - Additional feedback

## Deployment

This app is deployed as part of the Databricks Asset Bundle.

### Step 1: Set the serving endpoint (required)

The app reads the agent serving endpoint name from the bundle variable `agent_serving_endpoint`. Set it in your target (e.g. in `databricks.yml` under `targets.dev.variables`) to the name of the endpoint created by the model serving notebook, then deploy.

### Step 2: Deploy the Bundle

```bash
databricks bundle deploy -t dev
```

This will create/update the app definition, sync the app source code, and set `SERVING_ENDPOINT` from `agent_serving_endpoint` (via the app resource `config.env`). If `agent_serving_endpoint` is empty, the app will not start until you set it and redeploy.

### Step 3: Start the App

**Important**: Bundle deploy does NOT automatically start the app. You must start it manually:

```bash
# Option 1: Using Databricks CLI (use the actual app name for your bundle/target, e.g. dev-<project>-chatbot)
databricks apps start dev-{{ .input_project_name | replace "_" "-" }}-chatbot

# Option 2: Using the Workspace UI
# Navigate to Workspace > Apps > [your app name] > Click "Start"
```

### App name pattern

The app name is `{target}-{app_name}` where `app_name` is a dash-only segment (e.g. `{{ .input_project_name | replace "_" "-" }}-chatbot`). Examples:

- Dev: `dev-{{ .input_project_name | replace "_" "-" }}-chatbot`
- Staging: `staging-{{ .input_project_name | replace "_" "-" }}-chatbot`
- Prod: `prod-{{ .input_project_name | replace "_" "-" }}-chatbot`

### Verifying deployment

After starting the app, check its status:

```bash
# Check app status (use your app name)
databricks apps get dev-{{ .input_project_name | replace "_" "-" }}-chatbot

# View app logs (if needed)
databricks apps logs dev-{{ .input_project_name | replace "_" "-" }}-chatbot
```